Sierra Leone entered[ a 42-day
countdown](http://www.un.org/apps/news/story.asp?NewsID=51732#.Vd8dqyWqpHy) on
25 August 2015 to being declared Ebola free after the countryâ€™s last known
Ebola patient, Adama Sankoh, [was released from
hospital](http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2015/08/sierra-leone-ebola-patient-
leaves-hospital-150825143158511.html).

As of that day, the Ebola outbreak [had killed
3,952](http://apps.who.int/ebola/ebola-situation-reports) in the [West African
nation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ebola_virus_epidemic_in_Sierra_Leone),
according to the World Health Organisation.

Medical workers at the International Medical Corps treatment center in Makeni,
the third largest city in Sierra Leone, danced and sang to mark the occasion.
Watch the YouTube video above posted by the International Medical Corps
showing the staff's celebrations.

